12_plot_angle_rads


  1. Question

    Which graph shows an angle measuring \(\frac{4\pi}{11}\) radians in standard position?



    1. A
    2. B
    3. C
    4. D
    5. E
    6. F
    7. G
    8. H

    Solution

    The given angle is \(\frac{4\pi}{11}\) radians. The angle is positive, so the angle rotates counterclockwise. I prefer to think of this as \(4\) times \(\frac{\pi}{11}\), so then I imagine the top semicircle (and bottom semicircle) broken up into 11 equally-spaced wedges.
